From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Joey Pongallo <joeypongallo@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 02:40:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/xe: expose voltage-frequency curve + memory-speed OC via sysfs

Battlemage discrete GPUs (e.g. Arc Pro B60/B70) expose an 85-point
voltage-frequency (VF) curve through the PCODE "late-binding" interface.
Each point is a frequency step whose value is the voltage (mV). The
vendor driver programs this curve to implement the overclock / undervolt
controls in its tuning UI, but xe never issues the sequence, so VF-curve
tuning is unavailable on Linux even though the hardware and PCODE support
it identically to Windows.

Writing the curve is a bracketed PCODE transaction:

    PCODE_MBOX(0x5f, 2, 0)             begin write session
    PCODE_MBOX(0x5d, 0xa, 3) DATA0=P   write point P = (mV << 8 | index), x85
    PCODE_MBOX(0x5d, 0xb, 3)           end / finalize

A point is read with PCODE_MBOX(0x5d, 8, 3), DATA0=index -> DATA0=point.
The begin command is the key: without it, the per-point write is rejected
by PCODE (mailbox "illegal subcommand"). The LATE_BINDING capability
(PCODE 0x5c) and the per-point reads are identical on Linux and Windows;
only the begin/write/end transaction was missing.

Add a small "oc" sysfs group under the root tile's primary GT with a
read/write "vf_curve" attribute:

    <device>/tile0/gt0/oc/vf_curve

Reading emits one "<index> <voltage_mV>" line per point. Writing accepts
one or more such lines; unlisted points keep their current value and the
voltage is clamped to a conservative [400, 1200] mV window. The whole
transaction runs under a runtime-PM reference so it works while the GPU
is autosuspended.

A second attribute exposes the GDDR6 memory data rate:

    <device>/tile0/gt0/oc/mem_speed

in Mbps (19000 = 19 Gbps), via LATE_BINDING domain 0x17 -- write
PCODE_MBOX(0x5e, 6, 0x17) DATA0=Mbps then commit PCODE_MBOX(0x5e, 8, 0x17);
read PCODE_MBOX(0x5e, 5, 0x17). Clamped to [14000, 24000] Mbps.

The transactions and packing were derived by tracing the vendor driver's
PCODE mailbox activity (igdkmdnd64 fn issuing the mailbox writes) and
confirmed by replaying them on an Arc Pro B60: reads match the vendor
values, a written point/speed reads back changed, and reset restores
cleanly with no instability.

Signed-off-by: Joey Pongallo <joeypongallo@gmail.com>
---
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Makefile   |   1 +
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt.c    |   5 ++
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.c | 185 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h |  13 +++
 4 files changed, 204 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.c
 create mode 100644 drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Makefile b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Makefile
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Makefile
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/Makefile
@@ -56,6 +56,7 @@ xe-y += \
 	xe_gt_clock.o \
 	xe_gt_freq.o \
+	xe_gt_oc.o \
 	xe_gt_idle.o \
 	xe_gt_mcr.o \
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt.c
index 3333333..4444444 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt.c
@@ -29,6 +29,7 @@
 #include "xe_gt_clock.h"
 #include "xe_gt_freq.h"
+#include "xe_gt_oc.h"
 #include "xe_gt_idle.h"
@@ -697,6 +698,10 @@ int xe_gt_init(struct xe_gt *gt)
 	err = xe_gt_freq_init(gt);
 	if (err)
 		return err;

+	err = xe_gt_oc_init(gt);
+	if (err)
+		return err;
+
 	xe_force_wake_init_engines(gt, gt_to_fw(gt));
diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..5555555
--- /dev/null
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h
@@ -0,0 +1,13 @@
+/* SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT */
+/*
+ * Copyright © 2026 Intel Corporation
+ */
+
+#ifndef _XE_GT_OC_H_
+#define _XE_GT_OC_H_
+
+struct xe_gt;
+
+int xe_gt_oc_init(struct xe_gt *gt);
+
+#endif /* _XE_GT_OC_H_ */
--
2.43.0

NOTE: xe_gt_oc.c is provided in full as xe_gt_oc.c in this directory (185
lines). Regenerate this patch against the target tree with:
  git add drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.c drivers/gpu/drm/xe/xe_gt_oc.h
  git commit -s   # paste the message above
  git format-patch -1
so the hunk offsets match the destination kernel version.
